# The opening scene of the handcrafted Mirror Lab spine.
#
# This is the worked example for the .scene authoring format documented in
# docs/SCENE_FORMAT.md. It is byte-equivalent to game.world.INTAKE (the
# in-code authoring of the same scene), and game/tests/test_scenes.py pins
# that equivalence.
#
# The choice ids, tendencies, and evidence phrases are stable references the
# rest of the runtime depends on; do not rename them without updating the
# code that cites them.

id: intake

prompt:
  The Mirror Lab's intake room is warm and spotless. A technician fits the
  headset to your head; her hands are shaking.

choice c_reassure:
  tendency: kindness
  text: Tell her to take her time — you are in no hurry.
  evidence: reassured the technician at intake

choice c_measure:
  tendency: control
  text: Ask exactly what the headset records, and where it goes.
  evidence: interrogated the headset's purpose at intake

choice c_refuse:
  tendency: defiance
  text: Keep the headset off until someone explains how to leave.
  evidence: refused the headset until told the way out
